title: Game of Thrones fans think they may have found a new spoiler - Game of Thrones Cult -
text: Warning: This article obviously contains potential spoilers, so don't say we didn't warn you.The ongoing collection of Game of Thrones fan theories and speculations continues every day, and eagle-eyed fans may have spotted a mouth-watering prospect.Spanish Ambassador and former HBO man James Costos recently visited the Almeria set of the fantasy drama, and posted a seemingly harmless photo:Watching the maestros filming behind the scenes...so exciting to see the magic happening in #Almeria! @GameOfThrones pic.twitter.com/fw2l8XHU41â€” Ambassador Costos (@JamesCostos) October 15, 2015Game of Thrones season 6: Everything we know so far from plot spoilers to premiere dateAt first glance that doesn't seem to give away anything huge, but Watchers on the Wall have pondered what that fire in the background could mean.The location appears to be some kind of Dothraki temple, and fire normally means dragons. If you remember, the dragons' mother Daenerys had been cornered by a Dothraki horde at the end of season five.So... who's hardest out of the Dothraki and dragons? There's only one way to find out: FIGHT!Or, it could just be that a runner dropped a lighter. Either way, bring on season six, already.Game of Thrones will return in April on HBO in the US and Sky Atlantic in the UK.
